<font color="#FF0000">NOTE TO SEARCHING FOR FRIENDS</font><br>
<tt>Mon Aug 11 21:15:04 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Note to &quot;Doc Vincent&quot; of Searching for Friends.  Did not know you but served at Phantiet in 2nd/7th Battalion of 1st Cav from sometime in Aug.,66 to July, 67 as an RTO in Alpha Co. Was shot in Sept. 66 but did not miss any action. For 30 years I have wanted to thank someone in artillery for all the fine artillery support on all of our patrols out of Phantiet.  Your cooks also made the best breakfast around.  Never heard of fritters until artillery boys fixed them for us one day.  You guys sure knew how to eat.  Thanks for the support and the chow.  Mike
<p><code>-- MEKTT  (Mike Kovitch) </code><p>


